4 On page 2, delete lines 7 through 12 and insert:
5 “(3) The coverage required by subsection (2) of this section:
6 “(a) Includes, but is not limited to:
7 “(A) A minimum of three completed oocyte retrievals with unlimited
8 embryo transfers in accordance with guidelines of the American Society for
9 Reproductive Medicine, or a successor organization, using single embryo
10 transfer if recommended by a licensed treating practitioner and medically
11 effective.
12 “(B) Six completed egg retrievals per lifetime, with unlimited embryo
13 transfers in accordance with the guidelines of the American Society for Re-
14 productive Medicine, using single embryo transfer when recommended and
15 medically appropriate.
16 “(C) Assisted hatching.
17 “(D) Cryopreservation and thawing of embryos.
18 “(E) Embryo biopsy.
19 “(F) Fresh and frozen embryo transfers.
20 “(G) Storage of embryos.
21 “(H) In vitro fertilization, including in vitro fertilization using donor

1 eggs, sperm or embryos, and in vitro fertilization in which the embryo is
2 transferred to a gestational carrier or surrogate.
3 “(I) Intracytoplasmic sperm injection.
4 “(J) Storage of oocytes, sperm and tissue.
5 “(K) Intrauterine insemination.
6 “(L) Cryopreservation of ovarian tissue.
7 “(M) Cryopreservation of testicular tissue.
8 “(N) Cryopreservation and thawing of eggs and sperm.
9 “(O) Consultation and diagnostic testing.
10 “(P) Medications.
11 “(Q) Ovulation induction.
12 “(R) Surgery, including microsurgical sperm aspiration.
13 “(S) Medical and laboratory services that reduce excess embryo creation
14 through egg cryopreservation and thawing.”.
15 After line 26, insert:
16 “(6) This section does not require a health benefit plan offered by an
17 insurer described in ORS 743A.067 (7)(e) to reimburse the cost of:
18 “(a) Embryo transfer procedures as part of the coverages described in
19 subsection (3)(a)(A) and (B) of this section; and
20 “(b) Procedures described in subsection (3)(a)(C) to (I) of this section.
21 “(7) The coverage requirements described in this section do not apply to
22 health benefit plans offered by the Oregon Educators Benefit Board and
23 Public Employees’ Benefit Board, unless the Oregon Educators Benefit Board
24 or Public Employees’ Benefit Board elect to provide the coverage.”.
25 In line 27, delete “(6)” and insert “(8)”.
26 Delete lines 28 through 45.
