Proposed Amendments to HB 4155 Page 2

1 “SECTION 4. (1) The Department of Consumer and Business Ser-
2 vices shall administer a program to provide reimbursement for the
3 costs of procedures described in section 2 (6) of this 2026 Act that are
4 incurred by individuals enrolled in health benefit plans described in
5 ORS 743A.067 (7)(e). The department shall establish application pro-
6 cesses for the program and contract with a third party administrator
7 or health insurance carrier to process claims for enrollees in the pro-
8 gram.
9 “(2) The department may adopt rules necessary to carry out the
10 provisions of this section.
11 “SECTION 5. The Family Building Fund is established in the State
12 Treasury, separate and distinct from the General Fund, consisting of
13 moneys collected from the portion of assessments imposed under ORS
14 731.804 (3) for the costs of administering the program described in
15 section 4 of this 2026 Act. Interest earned by the Family Building Fund
16 shall be credited to the fund. Moneys in the Family Building Fund are
17 continuously appropriated to the Department of Consumer and Busi-
18 ness Services to carry out the provisions of section 4 of this 2026 Act.
19 “SECTION 6. ORS 731.292 is amended to read:
20 “731.292. (1) Except as provided in subsections (2), (3), [and] (4) and (5)
21 of this section, all fees, charges and other moneys received by the Depart-
22 ment of Consumer and Business Services or the Director of the Department
23 of Consumer and Business Services under the Insurance Code shall be de-
24 posited in the fund created by ORS 705.145 and are continuously appropriated
25 to the department for the payment of the expenses of the department in
26 carrying out the Insurance Code.
27 “(2) All taxes and penalties paid pursuant to the Insurance Code shall be
28 paid to the director and after deductions of refunds shall be paid by the di-
29 rector to the State Treasurer, at the end of every calendar month or more
30 often in the director’s discretion, for deposit in the General Fund to become
