14 Laws 2025, is amended to read:
15 “731.292. (1) Except as provided in subsections (2), (3) and (4) of this sec-
16 tion, all fees, charges and other moneys received by the Department of Con-
17 sumer and Business Services or the Director of the Department of Consumer
18 and Business Services under the Insurance Code shall be deposited in the
19 fund created by ORS 705.145 and are continuously appropriated to the de-
20 partment for the payment of the expenses of the department in carrying out
21 the Insurance Code.
22 “(2) All taxes and penalties paid pursuant to the Insurance Code shall be
23 paid to the director and after deductions of refunds shall be paid by the di-
24 rector to the State Treasurer, at the end of every calendar month or more
25 often in the director’s discretion, for deposit in the General Fund to become
26 available for general governmental expenses.
27 “(3) All premium taxes received by the director pursuant to ORS 731.820
28 shall be paid by the director to the State Treasurer for deposit in the State
29 Fire Marshal Fund.
30 “(4) Assessments received by the department under ORS 731.804 (3)
