Proposed Amendments to HB 4155 Page 4

1 shall be paid to the Family Building Fund established under section 5
2 of this 2026 Act.
3 “SECTION 8. ORS 731.804 is amended to read:
4 “731.804. (1) Except as otherwise provided in this section, each authorized
5 insurer doing business in this state shall pay assessments that the Director
6 of the Department of Consumer and Business Services determines are neces-
7 sary to support the legislatively authorized budget of the Department of
8 Consumer and Business Services with respect to functions of the department
9 under the Insurance Code. The director shall determine the assessments ac-
10 cording to one or more percentage rates established by the director by rule.
11 The director shall specify in the rule when assessments shall be made and
12 payments shall be due. The premium-weighted average of the percentage
13 rates may not exceed nine-hundredths of one percent of the gross amount of
14 premiums received by an insurer or the insurer’s insurance producers from
15 and under the insurer’s policies covering direct domestic risks, after deduct-
16 ing the amount of return premiums paid and the amount of dividend pay-
17 ments made to policyholders with respect to such policies. In the case of
18 reciprocal insurers, the amount of savings paid or credited to the accounts
19 of subscribers shall be deducted from the gross amount of premiums. In es-
20 tablishing the percentage rate or rates, the director shall use the most recent
21 premium data approved by the director. In establishing the amounts to be
22 collected under this subsection, the director shall take into consideration the
23 expenses of the department for administering the Insurance Code and the
24 fees collected under subsection (2) of this section. When the director estab-
25 lishes two or more percentage rates:
26 “(a) Each rate shall be based on such expenses of the department ascribed
27 by the director to the line of insurance for which the rate is established.
28 “(b) Each rate shall be applied to the gross amount of premium received
29 by an insurer or its insurance producers for the applicable line of insurance
30 as provided in this subsection.
HB 4155-6 2/13/26
Proposed Amendments to HB 4155 Page 5

1 “(2) The director may collect fees for specific services provided by the
2 department under the Insurance Code according to a schedule of fees estab-
3 lished by the director by rule. The director may collect such fees in advance.
4 In establishing the schedule for fees, the director shall take into consider-
5 ation the cost of each service for which a fee is imposed.
6 “(3)(a) Notwithstanding the provisions of ORS 743A.067 (7)(e) and
7 743A.067 (9), for the purpose of mitigating inequity in the health insurance
8 market, the director may assess a fee on any insurer that offers a health
9 benefit plan, as defined in ORS 743B.005, that is exempt from a provision of
10 ORS chapter 743A or other provision of the Insurance Code that requires
11 specified coverage by health benefit plans.
12 “(b) Any fees collected under paragraph (a) of this subsection must be the
13 actuarial equivalent of costs attributed to the provision and administration
14 of the required coverage by an insurer that is not exempt.
15 “(c) Nothing in this section limits the authority of the director to enforce
16 the provisions of ORS chapter 743A if an insurer unlawfully fails to comply.
17 “(d) Notwithstanding ORS 646A.628, fees paid in accordance with para-
18 graph (a) of this subsection shall be deposited in the [General Fund to become
19 available for general governmental expenses] Family Building Fund estab-
20 lished under section 5 of this 2026 Act.
21 “(4) Establishment and amendment of the schedule of fees under sub-
22 section (2) of this section are subject to prior approval of the Oregon De-
23 partment of Administrative Services and shall be within the budget
24 authorized by the Legislative Assembly as that budget may be modified by
25 the Emergency Board.
26 “(5) The director may not collect an assessment under subsection (1) of
27 this section from any of the following persons:
28 “(a) A fraternal benefit society complying with ORS chapter 748.
29 “(b) Any person or class of persons designated by the director by rule.
30 “(6) The director may not collect an assessment under subsection (1) of
HB 4155-6 2/13/26
Proposed Amendments to HB 4155 Page 6

1 this section with respect to premiums received from any of the following
2 policies:
3 “(a) Workers’ compensation insurance policies.
4 “(b) Wet marine and transportation insurance policies.
5 “(c) Any category of policies designated by the director by rule.”.
